SIMPLE: intersect
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intersect
<hw>In`ter*sect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Intersected</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Intersecting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>intersectus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>intersecare</ets> to intersect; <ets>inter</ets> +
<ets>secare</ets> to cut. See <er>Section</er>.]</ety> <def>To cut into
or between; to cut or cross mutually; to divide into parts; <as>as, any
two diameters of a circle <ex>intersect</ex> each other at the
center</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lands <qex>intersected</qex> by a narrow frith⟦br⟧
Abhor each other.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intersect</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intersect
<hw>In`ter*sect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To cut into
one another; to meet and cross each other; <as>as, the point where two
lines <ex>intersect</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>intersecting</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>intersectant</ent>⟦br⟧
